This paper focuses on the development of crowdsourced query processing systems, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a hybrid human-machine approach, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and utilizes machine learning techniques (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of crowdsourcing labeling, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social computing (cs.SI).
